createenchantablemachinery.createenchantablemachinery.ponder.mechan: Enchanting to Mechanical Drill
Like other tools, the Mechanical Drill can be enchanted by an enchanting table or anvil
Efficiency enchantments can increase the mining speed of mechanical drills...
Silk touch mining can also be used
The Mechanical Drill can receive any enchantment applicable to mining tools
When wearing Engineers' Goggles, the player can view the drill's enchantments
Enchanting to Mechanical Saw
Like other tools, the Mechanical Saw can be enchanted by an enchanting table or anvil
Efficiency enchantments can increase the processing efficiency of items
Of course, enchantments can also be applied to logging
Using a Mechanical Saw with a silk touch enchantment...
The enchantment effect allows you to fell trees
The Mechanical Saw can receive any enchantment applicable to mining tools
When wearing Engineers' Goggles, the player can view the saw's enchantments
Enchanting to Mechanical Harvester
Like other tools, the Mechanical Harvester can be enchanted by an enchanting table or anvil
It can be enchanted with silk touch effects, and...
Fortune enchantments can yield more crops
Any enchantment applicable to mining tools can be applied to the Mechanical Harvester
When wearing Engineers' Goggles, the applied enchantments can be viewed
Enchanting to Mechanical Plough
Like other tools, the Mechanical Plough can be enchanted
Efficiency enchantments can increase the mining speed of the Mechanical Plough
Any enchantment for mining tools can be applied to the Mechanical Plough
When wearing Engineers' Goggles, you can view the applied enchantments

fdbosses.fdbosses.bosses.description.chesed:
A creature born out of rocks corroded by sculk. Wields enormous magic power.

§cRecommended weapon type: {{(fdlib:item)item=minecraft:diamond_axe}}
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.chesed.mightiness_descri:
Chesed cannot be hurt directly and its arena cannot be easily escaped from.

All damage inflicted by Chesed cannot be lowered by any resistances.

Gives all combatants {{(fdbosses:effect)id=minecraft:night_vision}} while alive.

If a player looks away from Chesed, that player is inflicted with {{(fdbosses:effect)id=fdbosses:chesed_gaze}}.

Chesed proceeds to second phase when hp drop below 50%.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.chesed.blocks_descriptio: Tears out blocks from the earth and hurls them onto target.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.chesed.earthquake_descri:
Slams the earth emitting a shockwave and lightnings that travel out from Chesed position.

During second phase more lightnings are summoned and their movement speed is increased.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.chesed.espheres_descript:
Releases ball lightnings that travel out from Chesed.

These ball lightnings cannot be reflected.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.chesed.monoliths_descrip:
Spawns 4 monoliths when summoned. 

Monoliths deactivate upon death and cannot be damaged anymore.

Monoliths gain additional {{(fdbosses:config_float) config=chesedConfig, value=additionalSecondPhaseMonolithHP}} HP on second phase.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.chesed.roll_description:
Rolls around the arena damaging and pushing away everyone who step in its way. 

During second phase leaves a fire trail behind.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.chesed.rockfall_descript:
Fires lightning beam at the ceiling causing it to crumble while summoning lightnings around combatants. 

During second phase amount and frequency of lightnings are increased.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.chesed.lightning_ray_des:
Casts Crystals ability before this ability and then begins to fire lightning rays with tremendous power at target. 

Lightning ray deals 0 damage to targets affected by {{(fdbosses:effect)id=fdbosses:chesed_energized}}.

If a target is a charged ray reflector Chesed takes 1 damage.

During second phase the frequency of attacks is increased.

§lTip!§r

While charging the attack, Chesed tries to aim slightly beyond the target movement and stops aiming moments before releasing the lightning ray.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.chesed.final_description:
Drains power from monoliths and then unleashes a lightning strike that damage everyone on the battlefield. 

Amount of damage depends on how many monoliths are in an active state. 

While Chesed casts this ability, monoliths are invulnerable. 

Deactivated monoliths become active again after this ability ends.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.chesed.final_stats:
Attack: 
{{(fdlib:image)path=fdbosses:boss_damage}}: {{(fdbosses:config_float) config=chesedConfig, value=finalAttackDamagePercentPerMonolith}}% Max HP per active monolith.
fdbosses.fdbosses.word.stop_it: Stop it. Bosses do have feelings too, you know.
fdbosses.fdbosses.word.you_are_getting_on_my_nerv: You are starting to get on my nerves.
fdbosses.fdbosses.word.consequences: You will soon face the consequences of your own actions.
fdbosses.fdbosses.word.killed_chesed_in_screen: Well, you killed him. Congratulations! I hope you feel bad about yourself for killing an innocent creature! You know, i wanted to crash the game but that would be a bad game design, so i will leave that decision to you. Here, press that button.
fdbosses.fdbosses.boss_drop.fdbosses.chesed.fdbos:
A core that Chesed draws its power from. 

Can be applied to any weapon in crafting table. 

When attacking entities with a weapon that is enhanced with Lightning Core there is a chance to struck the target with Chesed lightning that will do a percentage of weapons damage while inflicting {{(fdbosses:effect)id=fdbosses:shocked}}.

Shock:
{{(fdlib:image)path=fdbosses:boss_damage}}: {{(fdbosses:config_float) config=effectConfig, value=shockDamageReductionPercent}}% outgoing damage reduction.
{{(fdlib:image)path=fdbosses:boss_duration}}: {{(fdbosses:config_float) config=itemConfig, value=lightningStrikeShockDuration}} ticks.

Lightning: 
{{(fdlib:image)path=fdbosses:boss_damage}}: {{(fdbosses:config_float) config=itemConfig, value=lightningStrikeDamagePercent}}% of weapon damage.

Summon chance:  {{(fdbosses:config_float) config=itemConfig, value=chanceToSummonLightningStrike}}%
A trophy of Chesed to showcase your heroic deeds
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.chesed.electrified_air_d: Air above Chesed crackles with power. Entities that interact with it are damaged.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.chesed.electrified_air_s:
Air: 
{{(fdlib:image)path=fdbosses:boss_damage}}: {{(fdbosses:config_float) config=chesedConfig, value=electrifiedAirCurrentHealthDamagePercent}}% current HP.

Instantly kills affected entity if HP is lower than  {{(fdbosses:config_float) config=chesedConfig, value=electrifiedAirInstadeathHP}}.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.chesed.kinetic_field_des:
Uses this attack only on second phase.

Traps players in a kinetic field that doesn't allow them to escape.

Periodically summons lightnings in all kinetic fields.
fdbosses.fdbosses.word.didnt_read_skills: It is highly advised to read boss skill descriptions before the fight. Do you really wish to start the fight now?
Consumed by rage, betrayed by life, now rests in peace the kingdoms tsar
fdbosses.fdbosses.word.tried_to_break_arena: An evil force prevents you from corrupting this place.
fdbosses.fdbosses.tldr.chesed:
Chesed damage pierces armor and shields.

To damage Chesed:

Wait until lightning ray attack, kill a crystal with an axe to get {{(fdbosses:effect)id=fdbosses:chesed_energized,level=1}}, run to a ray reflector and make Chesed hit it. You are immune to lightning ray attack when you are {{(fdbosses:effect)id=fdbosses:chesed_energized}}.

Chesed has an attack which damage depends on the amount of active monoliths, if all monoliths are active - there is no way to survive the attack. To deactivate a monolith - kill it.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.malkuth.fire_and_ice_des:
While on an arena combatants may be weak to §cFire§r or §bIce§r.

Current damage type you are weak to can be seen on the crosshair.

Malkuth abilities deal three types of damage:

1: §7Basic§r - regular damage type.

2: §cFire§r - makes targets weaker to §cFire§r damage, deals reduced damage to targets that are weak to §bIce§r.

3: §bIce§r - makes targets weaker to §bIce§r damage, deals reduced damage to targets that are weak to §cFire§r.

§lExample:§r

If target that is weak to §cFire§r receives §bIce§r damage, its amount is reduced and that target becomes weaker to §cFire§r.

If target that is weak to §cFire§r receives §cFire§r damage, its amount is not reduced and target becomes weaker to §cFire§r.
fdbosses.fdbosses.bosses.description.malkuth:
The Qliphoth of Malkuth. Benevolent King who ruled over a once-prosperous land, whose blind, excessive generosity became his kingdoms demise.

§5Devs Note: Its better to fight him at night.§r
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.malkuth.slash_descriptio:
Damage type: §cFire§r / §bIce§r

Charges one if his swords and releases an aerial slash traveling towards the target.

The damage type of the slash is based on the sword that was charged.

This slash is capable of slicing through crystals.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.malkuth.knights_duty_des:
During the bossfight all combatants receive {{(fdbosses:effect)id=fdbosses:knight}} .

When combatant escapes the arena before the fight ended {{(fdbosses:effect)id=fdbosses:knight}} transforms into {{(fdbosses:effect)id=fdbosses:coward}} .

Lava field is not a part of the arena!

When a combatant with {{(fdbosses:effect)id=fdbosses:coward}} steps into arena once again, it changes back to {{(fdbosses:effect)id=fdbosses:knight}}.

§oCowardness is not allowed! Death penalty!§r
fdbosses.effect_description.fdbosses.coward: When this effect expires immediately kills the owner
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.malkuth.armor_descriptio: Malkuth wields impenetrable armor, capable of neglecting any damage.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.malkuth.cannons_descript:
Damage type: §cFire§r / §bIce§r

Malkuth jumps on the wall behind him and orders his cannons to fire devastating shots at the target.

When this ability is cast, combatants cannons can be used once again, unless they are broken.

§lSecond phase:§r

When second phase starts Malkuth orders his cannons to break cannons on combatants side.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.malkuth.fair_duel_descri:
Combatants can use two cannons on their side to fight on equal ground with Malkuth.

Right click a cannon to fire a shot.

Combatants can only use the cannon of type they are currently weak to.

After firing a shot, cannon becomes unusable until the next use of Cannonade ability.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.malkuth.arcslash_descrip:
Damage type: §cFire§r / §bIce§r

Malkuth charges up his swords and releases aerial slashes in arcs, covering the whole arena.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.malkuth.side_rocks_descr:
Damage type: §cFire§r / §bIce§r

Malkuth tears up boulders from the earth, imbuing them with his magic and hurls them onto player.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.malkuth.impaling_doom_de:
Damage type: §cFire§r / §bIce§r

Malkuth slams the earth, releasing either a §cFire§r or §bIce§r spikes that travel in the slam direction.

When colliding with combatants those spikes hurl them up into the air.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.malkuth.earthshatter_des:
Damage type: §7Basic§r

Malkuth leaps to the target and crushes the earth, hurling everyone who were caught in the attack into the air.

During the second phase, if there are broken cannons on the combatants side, spawns a special crystal at the attack location that is capable of repairing cannons.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.malkuth.chainpunch_descr:
Damage type: §7Basic§r

Malkuth pulls every combatant, who were in the air, and punches them with overwhelming force.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.malkuth.tsars_wrath_stat:
Sword:
{{(fdlib:image)path=fdbosses:boss_damage}}: Infinite

This attacks damage can be fully negated, despite the damage reduction value.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.malkuth.tsars_wrath_desc:
Damage type: §cFire§r / §bIce§r

Malkuth summons two giant swords and orders them to slam the ground with devastating force.

§lSecond phase:§r

Also fires his cannons before the attack lands.
fdbosses.fdbosses.skills.malkuth.hellshaper_descr:
Damage type: §cFire§r / §bIce§r

Malkuth slams the earth, summoning floating islands, hurling everyone in the air and rendering the floor impossible to walk on.

Launches fireballs at these islands thereafter.
fdbosses.fdbosses.word.patreon: Support mod development on Patreon (Shift+Click to see Patrons)
fdbosses.fdbosses.word.boosty: Support mod development on Boosty (Shift+Click to see Boosters)
fdbosses.fdbosses.boss_drop.fdbosses.malkuth.fdbo:
Damage:
{{(fdlib:image)path=fdbosses:boss_damage}}: {{(fdbosses:config_float) config=itemConfig, value=playerMalkuthFireballToolDamagePercent}}% of tool damage.

Item ability cooldown:
{{(fdlib:image)path=fdbosses:boss_duration}}: {{(fdbosses:config_float) config=itemConfig, value=playerMalkuthFireballAbilityCooldown}} ticks

The core of Malkuth.

Can be attached to any item that has damage to be able to summon Malkuth fireballs.

Use an item to release a fireball that will deal a percentage of item damage and ignite the targets.

Crouch while using an item to release an iceball that will slow the targets instead.
A trophy of Malkuth to showcase your heroic deeds
fdbosses.fdbosses.tldr.malkuth:
Cannot be attacked directly.

When player is weak to §cFire§r it receives decreased §bIce§r damage, and other way around if player is weak to §bIce§r, it receives decreased §cFire§r damage.

Current weakness can be seen on the crosshair.

Use cannons on the arena to attack Malkuth, you can only use the cannon of type you are currently weak to.

ftbbackups3.ftbbackups3.general.auto.tooltip: Run backups automatically, based on the "Backup Timer" setting

ftbbackups3.ftbbackups3.general.display_file_size.to: When true (and "Run Silently" is false), also display backed-up file size to players
ftbbackups3.ftbbackups3.general.extra_files.tooltip:

World folder is "world" on a dedicated server,

ftbbackups3.ftbbackups3.general.max_total_size.toolt:
The maximum size to allow for backups.

ftbbackups3.ftbbackups3.general.only_if_players_onli: Automated backups are only run if at least one player is online
ftbbackups3.ftbbackups3.general.force_on_shutdown.to: If true (and "Automatic Backups" is true), always run a backup when the server is being stopped
ftbbackups3.ftbbackups3.general.archival_plugin.tool:
The plugin used to actually create files on disk.
Builtin options create ZIP files or flat file copies.
ftbbackups3.ftbbackups3.general.notify_admins_only.t:
If true, only admin-level players (and SSP server owners) are notified on-screen about current backup progress
If false, all players are notified
ftbbackups3.ftbbackups3.general.add_backup_command_a: If true, register a /backups command as an alias to /ftbbackups3
ftbbackups3.ftbbackups3.general.excluded_files.toolt:
Files which should not be added to the backup archive
File globs and regexes are both supported
Use `glob:<file-glob> or 'regex:<regular-expression>'
ftbbackups3.ftbbackups3.general.advanced.buffer_size:

ftbfiltersystem.filter.ftbfiltersystem.component.tooltip:

ftbfiltersystem.filter.ftbfiltersystem.food_value.name: Food Value
ftbfiltersystem.filter.ftbfiltersystem.food_value.toolti:

ftbfiltersystem.filter.ftbfiltersystem.item.name: Item
ftbfiltersystem.filter.ftbfiltersystem.item.tooltip:

ftbfiltersystem.filter.ftbfiltersystem.item_tag.name: Item Tag

ftbfiltersystem.filter.ftbfiltersystem.stack_size.name: Stack Size
ftbfiltersystem.filter.ftbfiltersystem.stack_size.toolti: Matches against an item's current stack size.
ftbfiltersystem.filter.ftbfiltersystem.max_stack_size.to:

ftbfiltersystem.filter.ftbfiltersystem.mod.name: Mod
ftbfiltersystem.filter.ftbfiltersystem.mod.tooltip:

Vanilla items are in the Minecraft 'mod'.
ftbfiltersystem.filter.ftbfiltersystem.custom.name: Custom
ftbfiltersystem.filter.ftbfiltersystem.custom.tooltip:
Advanced filter intended for modders and modpack makers.
Fires a CustomFilterEvent when a match is attempted; set the event result to indicate a successful or failed match.
Use the textfield to provide freeform text data which is passed to the event as the 'data' parameter.
ftbfiltersystem.filter.ftbfiltersystem.expression.name: Expression
ftbfiltersystem.filter.ftbfiltersystem.expression.toolti:

It is optional (but recommended!) to assign a custom name, for clarity.

gag.item.gag.hearthstone.info_adv: A stronger hearthstone that has channelled the energy of raw lightning, and can be used to teleport to a single bound location. You can reset the stone by hitting it with lightning again.
gag.item.gag.hearthstone.no_target: Couldn't find anywhere to teleport to, did you set your spawn point?
gag.item.gag.hearthstone.too_weak: It seems this hearthstone is too weak to call home from this place.
gag.item.gag.labeling_tool.info: Used to change the name of any item in your inventory at no cost.
gag.item.gag.mining_dynamite.info: Throwable explosive that has a high efficiency against stone. Drops all blocks it destroys.
gag.item.gag.pigment_jar.info.empty.1: An empty jar used to store pigments. Probably needs to be filled to be useful.
gag.item.gag.pigment_jar.info.empty.2: Hint: Grind up some dye with flint, then add some milk.
gag.item.gag.pigment_jar.info.filled.1: Can be used in a labeling tool to change the color of the item's name.
gag.item.gag.pigment_jar.info.filled.2: Hint: Combine with other pigment jars to mix colors.
gag.item.gag.sacred_balm.extra: Lasts considerably longer than either the salt or salve, but has a reduced radius.
gag.item.gag.sacred_salve.extra: Lasts a bit longer than the salt, and also works in a larger area.

gag.item.gag.time_sand_pouch.info: Slowly accumulates time while in a player's inventory. Use on a ticking block to accelerate it, using some of the stored time from the pouch.
gag.item.gag.time_sand_pouch.info.stored_gra: Contains %2$s worth of Grains of Time
gag.subtitles.gag.item.time_sand_pouch.dong: Block tick accelerated to very high speed

ironfurnaces.tooltip.ironfurnaces.xmas2: Sneaking and right-clicking on a furnace opens the gift
ironfurnaces.tooltip.ironfurnaces.spooky2: Sneaking and right-clicking on a furnace will cleanse any spookalizations
ironfurnaces.tooltip.ironfurnaces.heater_not_bound: Has yet to be bound to an energy source!

ironfurnaces.tooltip.ironfurnaces.heater_tip1: Only works from Iron tier and above

ironfurnaces.tooltip.ironfurnaces.augment_xp_1: Experience granted from smelting will given to the player that placed the furnace.
ironfurnaces.tooltip.ironfurnaces.augment_xp_switch: Sneak & Right click in the air to switch modes.

ironfurnaces.tooltip.ironfurnaces.augment_generator_p: +Heat from the furnace will generate power.
ironfurnaces.tooltip.ironfurnaces.augment_generator_c: -The furnace can no longer smelt items.
ironfurnaces.tooltip.ironfurnaces.heater_block: Link with a Wireless Heat Receiver (done by placing the receiver in the Wireless Heat Transmitter)
ironfurnaces.tooltip.ironfurnaces.heater_block1: Provide this block with Forge Energy and it will power all Wireless Heat Receivers that are bound

ironfurnaces.tooltip.ironfurnaces.rainbow_gen2: RF/tick if all other furnaces are generating power

ironfurnaces.tooltip.ironfurnaces.rainbow_gen4: Outputs energy to any side that is configured as output, it wont add energy to the internal buffer

irregular_implements.command.irregular_implements.spectre_ene: %s has %s FE in their Spectre Energy buffer.
Set %s's Spectre Energy buffer to %s FE.
irregular_implements.death.fell.accident.fluid_fall.boot: %s splattered against the surface of %s because they were wearing %s
irregular_implements.death.fell.accident.fluid_fall.generic: %s splattered against the surface of %s because they could walk on it
irregular_implements.enchantment.irregular_implements.magneti: Teleports fresh item drops towards you
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.accelerator_pl: Entities moving on this Plate are sped up slightly, to a limit.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.advanced_item_:
Collects items in a configurable radius and inserts it into the inventory it's placed on.

You can also insert an Item Filter for more control.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.advanced_redst:
Powers up to 9 linked blocks with the Redstone signal it's receiving.

Use a Redstone Tool to link it to blocks.
A Redstone Repeater that can have both its Step Up and Step Down delays configured.
A Redstone Torch that can have its Powered and Unpowered output strengths configured
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.analog_emitter: Emits a Redstone signal with a configurable strength when the front face is powered.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.auto_placer:
Places blocks in front of it from its inventory.

Can be disabled with a Redstone signal.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.basic_redstone:
Powers the linked block with the Redstone signal it's receiving.

Use a Redstone Tool to link it to a block.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.bean_pod:
Found at the top of a grown Magic Bean.

Contains loot!
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.biome_blocks: Changes color to match the biome.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.biome_capsule:
Throw on the ground, and it will capture the biome it lands in.

Used in conjunction with the Biome Painter.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.biome_crystal: Found in dungeon chests, can be inserted into a Biome Radar to locate a biome.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.biome_painter:
Use it on a block, and it will paint the biome of the first Biome Capsule in your inventory.

The radius can be configured.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.biome_radar:
Insert a Biome Crystal and provide a Redstone signal, and it will attempt to find the Crystal's biome.

If it succeeds, it will spawn particles aiming in its direction.

Using a Paper on it will create a Location Filter for the biome.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.blackout_powde: Removes the Spectre Illuminator in the chunk it's used in.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.blaze_and_stee: Lights a much more aggressive Fire.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.block_breaker:
Breaks blocks in front of it with the effectiveness of an Iron Pickaxe. Drops are inserted into the inventory behind it, or dropped.

Can be disabled with a Redstone signal.

Can be upgraded with a Diamond Breaker.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.block_destabil:
When given a Redstone pulse, scans the blocks in front of it.

It then gives the nearest 50 connected blocks gravity, making them fall.

You can set it to "lazy" mode, which makes it remember the shape, and only destabilize those blocks.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.block_mover:
Use on a block to pick it up, and use it again to place it.

Can be used on blocks with Block Entities, like Chests and machines.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.block_of_stick: Cheap building material that automatically breaks after 10 seconds.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.block_replacer:
Stores up to 9 stacks of blocks. When used on a block, it gets replaced with a random stored block.

Sneak right-click to open its inventory.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.bottle_of_air:
Refills your breath.

Can be found in Ocean Monuments.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.bouncy_plate: Entities on this Plate are propelled upwards.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.chat_detector: Emits a Redstone pulse if the block's owner sends a chat message containing some specified text.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.chunk_analyzer: When used, shows you all the blocks and entities in the chunk you're in.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.collection_pla:
Dropped item entities that pass over this Plate attempt to insert into adjacent inventories.

The order it tries is: Down, North, South, East, West, Up
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.compressed_sli:
Create by clicking a Slime Block with a Shovel. Can be compressed multiple times.

Launches entities into the air.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.contact_button: Acts like a Button, but works when the block in front of it is clicked instead.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.contact_lever: Acts like a Lever, but works when the block in front of it is clicked instead.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.corrector_plat:
Entities moving on the Plate are centered along the axis they're moving.

For example, if they're moving South, they're teleported to the middle of the North-South axis of the block.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.custom_craftin:
Works exactly like a vanilla Crafting Table, except it looks like the block it's made of.

This uses the item tag #irregular_implements:custom_crafting_table_items
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.diamond_breake:
Apply to a Block Breaker to increase its mining level to equivalent to a Diamond Pickaxe.

Can also be enchanted!
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.diaphanous_blo:
Looks like another block, but becomes transparent as you approach.

Craft it with any block to set its appearance.

Craft it by itself to invert it, so it starts transparent and becomes opaque.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.directional_ac: Entities on this Plate are pushed slightly in the direction the Plate is facing.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.divining_rod:
When held in hand, highlights the corresponding ore if it's within 20 blocks of you.

This radius can be configured.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.drop_filter: Filters out items that match the contained Item Filters from entering your inventory.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.ectoplasm:
Every time an entity dies, it has a chance of spawning a Spirit.

Spirits can only be killed by magic, and they drop Ectoplasm.

Can also be harvested from Spectre Trees.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.emerald_compas:
Points to the set player, if they are online.

Set the player by crafting with a Player Filter.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.ender_anchor: Destination point for the Ender Bridge or Prismarine Ender Bridge.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.ender_bridge:
Upon the Ender Bridge receiving a Redstone Signal, it looks for an Ender Anchor in front of it.

It searches at 20 blocks per second, and then teleports the player standing on top to it.

There's no distance limit, though there can be no blocks between (save for the block directly in front of the Bridge).
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.ender_bucket: When used on a non-source fluid, it picks up the nearest source.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.ender_letter:
Can be used to send items and messages to other players.

Type the name of the player at the top, and insert up to 9 items.

Click an Ender Mailbox, and it will be inserted into their Ender Mailbox if it has room.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.ender_mailbox: Allows players to send and receive Ender Letters.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.entity_detecto: Emits a Redstone signal if a configured entity is within a configured range.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.entity_filter: Allows you to filter by entity type. Do so by using it on an entity.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.escape_rope:
Hold right-click to begin searching for the nearest location that can see the sky.

If it finds one, it'll teleport you there.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.evil_tear:
Can be used on a specific structure to make an Artificial End Portal.

Place an End Stone, and place an End Rod under it.

4 blocks below it, build a 3x3 of End Stone, with a 5x5 ring of Obsidian one block above it.

Use the Evil Tear on the End Rod to complete the structure.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.extraction_pla:
Has an "input" side and an "output" side. Extracts stacks from the input side, and drops or inserts them on the output side, depending on if there's an inventory there.

Right-click with an empty hand to change the output side, and do so while sneaking to change the input side.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.fertilized_dir:
Fertilized Dirt does not require hydration, grows crops 3 times faster, and can't be trampled.

You still have to till it with a Hoe to grow crops.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.filtered_redir:
Has two "input" sides, and two color-coded "output" sides.

Both output sides have a slot for an Entity Filter, and any entity that enters from the input sides are teleported to the output with a matching Filter.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.global_chat_de:
Emits a redstone pulse if any player sends a chat message containing the specified text.

Can have a player whitelist using Player Filterss.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.golden_egg:
Spawns a Chicken that lays Gold Ingots rather than Eggs.

Can be found in Bean Pods, which can be found at the top of Bean Stalks grown from Magic Beans.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.grass_seeds: Can be planted on Dirt to grow Grass.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.igniter:
Sets or extinguishes the block on front of it, depending on the Redstone signal.

Can be set to keep the fire lit.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.imbue_collapse:
Inverts your controls.

Why would you want this?
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.imbue_experien:
Increases experience dropped by entities by 50%%.

Lasts 20 minutes, but you can only have one Imbuement at a time.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.imbue_fire:
Sets entities you hit with melee attacks on fire.

Lasts 20 minutes, but you can only have one Imbuement at a time.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.imbue_poison:
Inflicts Poison II on entities you hit with melee attacks.

Lasts 20 minutes, but you can only have one Imbuement at a time.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.imbue_spectre:
Gives you a configurable chance to fully negate damage.

Lasts 20 minutes, but you can only have one Imbuement at a time.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.imbue_wither:
Inflicts Wither II on entities you hit with melee attacks.

Lasts 20 minutes, but you can only have one Imbuement at a time.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.inventory_rero:
Each side can be configured to "point" to one side of the block in front.

For example, setting this block's bottom face to "U" will and then inserting items into it will try to insert those items into the top face of the block in front of it.

Also allows for extracting.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.inventory_test:
When placed on an inventory, constantly simulates attempting to insert a configured Item Stack.

If the simulation would succeed, it emits a Redstone signal. You can invert this behavior.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.iron_dropper:
An upgraded Dropper, where the following can be configured:

• Item pickup delay
• Item motion randomness
• Particle/Sound toggle
• Redstone control
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.item_collector: Collects items in a 3 block radius and inserts it into the inventory it's placed on.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.item_filter: Allows you to filter Item Stacks. Do so in its GUI.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.item_rejuvenat: Dropped item entities that pass over this Plate have their despawn timer set to 4 minutes.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.item_sealer_pl: Dropped item entities that pass over this Plate cannot be picked up for 30 seconds.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.lapis_glass: Solid for players, not solid for anything else.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.lava_charm:
Adds a temporary lava shield, visible above your armor bar. This prevents taking damage from Lava, but does NOT prevent you from lighting on fire!

Lasts about 10 seconds.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.lava_waders:
Combines the effects of Obsidian Water Walking Boots and a Lava Charm.

Additionally allows you to stand on lava.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.lesser_magic_b:
Can be planted on any block, and grows into a bean stalk.

Bean Stalk blocks can be climbed faster than Ladders.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.location_filte:
An item representation of a position in the world.

Set by either using it on a block.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.lotus_blossom:
Grants experience when consumed.

Sneak to consume the entire stack.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.lotus_seeds:
Can be planted to grow Lotus Blossoms.

Lotus plants can be found in cold biomes.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.lubricant: Completely frictionless. Anything moving on it will retain its momentum.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.luminous_powde: Can be crafted onto items to make them glow in the dark.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.magic_bean:
Can be planted on any block, and grows a bean stalk that reaches the sky.

The top of the bean stalk has treasures.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.magic_hood: Disables your name plate and potion particles.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.magnetic_encha: Teleports fresh item drops towards you.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.moon_phase_det: Emits a Redstone signal depending on the current moon phase.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.notification_i: Sends a configurable toast notification to the block's owner when a Redstone signal is received.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.obsidian_skull:
Has a chance of negating fire damage.

The chance is higher the lower the damage would be.
Works like the Obsidian Skull, but can be worn as a Curio.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.obsidian_water: Combines the effects of the Obsidian Skull and Water Walking Boots.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.online_detecto: Emits a Redstone signal if the specified player is online.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.peace_candle:
Prevents natural mob spawns in a 3 chunk radius.

Can be found in roughly half of Villager Temples.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.pitcher_plant:
Acts as an infinite water source.

Slowly fills adjacent fluid containers.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.player_filter:
Acts like an Entity Filter, but specifically for the player set.

Set by using it in your hand.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.player_interfa: Exposes the inventory of the block's owner, as if it was the block's inventory.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.portable_ender:
Use while looking at an Ender Anchor to teleport to it.

Has a configurable range, defaulting to 300. Requires direct line of sight.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.portkey:
Use on a block to set a destination, then throw it on the ground.

After 5 seconds, anyone who picks it up will be teleported to the destination.

You can craft it with any other item to disguise it!
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.potion_vaporiz:
Allows you to fill a room with a potion effect.

Insert Potions and Furnace fuel, and it will scan the area in front of it to check if it's an enclosed area.

If it is, it'll fill it with the potion effect.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.prismarine_end:
Upon the Prismarine Ender Bridge receiving a Redstone Signal, it looks for an Ender Anchor in front of it (with no distance limit, though it must be loaded, and no other blocks can be in the way).

It searches at 200 blocks per second, and then teleports the player standing on top to it.

There's no distance limit, though there can be no blocks between (save for the block directly in front of the Bridge).
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.rain_shield: Prevents rain in a 5 chunk radius.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.rainbow_lamp:
Changes color depending on the Redstone signal strength.

Only the texture changes, the light stays the same color.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.redirector_pla: Has two "enabled" sides. Entities that enter from one side are sent to the other side.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.redstone_activ:
Using it on a block will give it a temporary Redstone signal.

Use it on the air to change the duration.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.redstone_obser:
Emits the same Redstone signal as a linked block.

Use a Redstone Tool to link it to a block.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.redstone_plate:
Entities moving over this plate are redirected in a configurable direction.

If powered, they instead move forward.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.redstone_remot:
Allows you to temporarily power one of nine blocks from a distance.

Sneak right-click it to open its GUI, where you can place up to 9 Location Filters. Under each you can set an item to represent that position.

Right-click normally to see all the positions it can power.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.redstone_tool:
Used to bind the Redstone Observer or Redstone Interfaces to blocks.

Sneak right-click on the Observer/Interface, then click on the block to bind/unbind it.

Also shows the signal strength of the block you're looking at!
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.reinforced_end:
Works like an Ender Bucket, but can hold 10 sources.

If sneaking, it will pick up as many sources as it can.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.returning_bloc: Works like a Block of Sticks, but teleports itself to the nearest player after breaking.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.sakanade_spore:
Found on the bottom of huge brown mushrooms.

Touching it inflicts you with Collapse for a short time, which inverts your controls.

This also inverts mobs' movement! They'll move the opposite direction they're trying to.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.shock_absorber: Reduces all fall damage, and also emits a redstone signal strength relative to the distance fallen.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.sided_redstone: Emits a Redstone signal on only one side.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.slime_cube:
Causes Slimes to spawn in great numbers in the chunk its in.

When powered, it instead prevents Slimes from spawning in the chunk.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.spectre_anchor: When crafted with an item, the item is kept after death.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.spectre_armor:
Comparable to Diamond Armor with higher durability and enchantability.

Also makes you slightly transparent!
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.spectre_axe:
Comparable to a Diamond Axe with higher durability and enchantability.

Increases the block reach of the player by 3 blocks.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.spectre_block: An indestructible block that spawns in the Spectre Dimension.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.spectre_charge:
Charges items in your inventory with an infinite amount of energy.

Creative only!
Charge items in your inventory using energy from your Spectre Energy Buffer.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.spectre_coil_b:
Outputs FE from the Spectre Energy Buffer, which is filled using Spectre Energy Injectors.

Has a rate of 1,024 FE/t.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.spectre_coil_e:
Outputs FE from the Spectre Energy Buffer, which is filled using Spectre Energy Injectors.

Has a rate of 20,480 FE/t.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.spectre_coil_g: Generates an infinite amount of FE for free, inserting it into the block it's placed on.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.spectre_coil_n: Generates 128 FE/t for free, inserting it into the block it's placed on.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.spectre_coil_r:
Outputs FE from the Spectre Energy Buffer, which is filled using Spectre Energy Injectors.

Has a rate of 4,096 FE/t.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.spectre_energy:
Acts like an Ender Chest for FE.

FE can be inserted into the Spectre Energy Injector, but Spectre Coils are required to extract it.

A player's Spectre Energy Buffer can store up to 1,000,000 FE by default.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.spectre_illumi:
When used, spawns a Spectre Illuminator that lights up the entire chunk.

Can be removed either by clicking the Illuminator, or using Blackout Powder in the chunk.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.spectre_key:
Use for 5 seconds to teleport to a private dimension.

Do the same there to return.
irregular_implements.info.irregular_implements.spectre_lens:

productivemetalworks.book.productivemetalworks.intro_page.bui: The blocks you will need to achieve your foundry are:$(br)* Foundry Controller$(br)* Foundry Tank$(br)* Liquid Heating Coils$(br)* Fire Bricks or Foundry Windows$(br)* Foundry Drain and Taps$(br)* Casting Basin & Table$(br2)The foundry can be as small as  1x1 and any rectangular shape. To the right you can see an example of a square 3x3 setup.
productivemetalworks.book.productivemetalworks.intro_page.cas: To get usable resources from the melted materials you need to cast ingots or blocks from them using the casting basin or table with a cast.$(br2)The Foundry can easily be automated by using a redstone pulse or clock on the tap or by replacing the tap with any other fluid transport pipe.
productivemetalworks.book.productivemetalworks.intro_page.met: Welcome to Productive Metalworks. A mod inspired by the Tinker's Construct Smeltery. You will find some differences, and lots of similarities. Do note, this mod is NOT a tool making mod, it is only the foundry.
productivemetalworks.book.productivemetalworks.intro_page.obt: In order to construct the Foundry you need fire bricks which are obtained by smelting fire clay. You will start by making the black fire bricks. The black versions of the blocks are the base ones and can be dyed to get the different colored ones.
productivemetalworks.book.productivemetalworks.intro_page.sge: Welcome to Productive Metalworks. A mod inspired by the Tinker's Construct Smeltery. You will find some differences, and lots of similarities. This mod does not add any tool or weapons but has compatibility with Silent Gear and modifies how you acquire gear parts. More on this in the $(l:sgear)SGear section$(/l).
productivemetalworks.book.productivemetalworks.intro_page.str: Be aware that the base level of the foundry will need to be made from heating coils. These enable you to actually heat up the foundry. The corners of the foundry multiblock are optional.$(br)The foundry by default will smelt raw ore at a 2x rate and the melting rate is determined by the fuel used. Check JEI for all the melting recipes
productivemetalworks.book.productivemetalworks.landing_text: A shallow look into the world of metalworking.$(br2)Put on your gloves 'cause it's gonna get hot.
productivemetalworks.book.productivemetalworks.name: Big Book of Metallurgy
productivemetalworks.book.productivemetalworks.sgear_category: Silent Gear casting with the Foundry.
productivemetalworks.book.productivemetalworks.sgear_page.cas: There's a gear cast for every gear type that requires casting, this includes tips and tool rods. Please note that the tool rod cast is different from the regular rod cast.
productivemetalworks.book.productivemetalworks.sgear_page.gra: There are a few other changes this mod makes to Silent Gear. The first one is the casting as already mentions, the other changes are that in order to grade or star charge your tool you have to do it to the final gear part and NOT the individual materials.Grading and star charging needs to be done on the gear part multiple times as it will act on each individual material in the part one at a time.
productivemetalworks.book.productivemetalworks.sgear_page.par: Gear parts that use materials which have a molten version will have to be cast in the foundry. You'll need a cast for each gear type, pickaxe, shovel, tip etc. To get a cast you have to make a gear part from simple materials like stone, wood, flint or bone, then use that gear part to make the cast.

productivemetalworks.productivemetalworks.ponder.foundry_cast: To turn the fluid into blocks you need to use a Casting Basin
