rarcompat.tooltip.relics.shock_pendant.leveling_so: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.thorn_pendant.description: Poisons anyone who dares to attack the relic bearer.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.thorn_pendant.ability.poi: Has a %3$s%% chance to reflect %1$s%% damage and apply poison to the target attacking the player for %2$s seconds.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.thorn_pendant.leveling_so: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.cowboy_hat.description: Enhances the agility of the relic bearer’s mounts.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.cowboy_hat.ability.cowboy: Increases the movement speed, jump height, and safe fall height of mounts by %1$s%%.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.cowboy_hat.ability.overlo: When used, this ability allows you to ride and control any mob for up to %1$s seconds. After the time expires or dismounting, it goes on a 1-minute cooldown.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.cowboy_hat.leveling_sourc: +%1$s experience points with a 25% chance for each second of riding.
+%1$s experience points for each use of the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.crystal_heart.description: Grants the relic bearer extra strength by increasing their maximum health.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.crystal_heart.ability.hea: Increases the player's maximum health by %1$s points.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.crystal_heart.leveling_so: +%1$s experience points for each instance of health regeneration. The probability of gaining experience is inversely proportional to the ratio of current health to maximum health.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.universal_attractor.descr: Manipulates a weak magnetic field around the relic bearer, controlling the gravity of nearby items.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.universal_attractor.abili: A toggleable ability with 3 modes: Attraction, Repulsion, and Neutrality. In the red Attraction mode, items within a radius of %1$s blocks are drawn toward the player. In the blue Repulsion mode, items are pushed away. The purple Neutrality mode disables the relic's effect.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.universal_attractor.level: +%1$s experience points for each item picked up using the %2$s ability. The probability of gaining experience is directly proportional to the ratio of current item count in the stack to its maximum capacity. Does not work if the item was dropped by the relic bearer.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.cross_necklace.descriptio: Envelops the relic bearer in a protective aura, granting temporary invulnerability after each hit taken.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.cross_necklace.ability.in: Increases the duration of invulnerability after taking damage by %1$s seconds.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.cross_necklace.leveling_s: +%1$s experience points for each instance of damage taken.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.night_vision_goggles.desc: Allows the relic bearer to see more clearly in the dark.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.night_vision_goggles.abil: Enhances the brightness of poorly lit areas and reduces the effectiveness of blindness and darkness by %1$s%%.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.night_vision_goggles.leve: +%1$s experience points for every 5 seconds of movement in darkness. The probability of gaining experience is directly proportional to the current light level ratio at the player's location to the maximum.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.cloud_in_a_bottle.descrip: Enhances the relic bearer's agility, allowing for additional jumps in the air.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.cloud_in_a_bottle.ability: Allows up to %1$s additional air jumps.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.cloud_in_a_bottle.levelin: +%1$s experience points for each additional jump performed using the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.vampiric_glove.descriptio: Grants the relic bearer's attacks a vampiric effect, healing them by a portion of the damage dealt.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.vampiric_glove.ability.va: Heals the player for %1$s%% of the damage dealt.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.vampiric_glove.leveling_s: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability. The probability of gaining experience is directly proportional to the ratio of healing received to the player's maximum health.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.golden_hook.description: Allows the relic bearer to perform more precise attacks, retaining more experience from killed mobs.
Increases experience gained from killing mobs by %1$s%%.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.golden_hook.leveling_sour: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.onion_ring.description: Enhances the relic bearer's block mining efficiency when sufficiently satiated.
Increases block mining speed by %1$s%% per unit of the player's saturation.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.onion_ring.ability.satura: When mining blocks, there is a %1$s%% chance to restore 1 hunger point and 0.5 saturation to the player.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.onion_ring.leveling_sourc: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
+%1$s experience points for each block mined. The chance of gaining experience is directly proportional to current saturation. Does not work on blocks with instant break.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.digging_claws.description: Strengthens the relic bearer's hands, allowing them to chop through any blocks more effectively.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.digging_claws.ability.pas: Reduces the required tool level for all blocks by 1.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.digging_claws.leveling_so: +%1$s experience points for each mined block. The probability of gaining experience is directly proportional to the block's toughness. Does not work on blocks with instant destruction.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.feral_claws.description: Awakens a bloodthirsty instinct in the relic bearer, making them fight faster with each consecutive attack.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.feral_claws.ability.claws: Increases the player's attack speed by %1$s%% for each consecutive attack performed within 3 seconds of the last. Otherwise, loses 1 charge per second. Attacking with an unfilled attack speed bar resets the accumulated charges.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.feral_claws.leveling_sour: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.antidote_vessel.descripti: Enhances the relic bearer's resistance to effects.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.antidote_vessel.ability.a: Reduces the duration of negative effects received by %1$s%%.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.antidote_vessel.ability.d: Each successful attack steals %1$s seconds from all positive effects present on the target.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.antidote_vessel.leveling_: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
+%1$s experience points for each effect stolen using the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.power_glove.description: Allows the relic bearer to perform empowered attacks.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.power_glove.ability.power: Increases the player's damage dealt by %1$s%% but enters a 5-second cooldown after each attack.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.power_glove.leveling_sour: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.withered_bracelet.descrip: Fills the relic bearer's weapon with withering energy, affecting all it touches.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.withered_bracelet.ability: Has a %1$s%% chance to apply the Wither effect to the attacked target for %2$s seconds.
Grants complete resistance to wither damage.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.withered_bracelet.levelin: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.snowshoes.description: Improves the relic bearer's mobility in harsh snowy conditions.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.snowshoes.ability.passive: Allows walking on powder snow without sinking.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.snowshoes.ability.speed.d: Increases movement speed on snow by %1$s%%.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.snowshoes.leveling_source: +%1$s experience points for every 3 seconds of movement on snow.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.steadfast_spikes.descript: Firmly anchors the relic bearer's feet to any surface.
Increases resistance to knockback and slippery blocks by %1$s%%.
Allows slow wall sliding, negating fall damage.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.steadfast_spikes.leveling: +%1$s experience points for each knockback reduced by the %2$s ability.
+%1$s experience points for every 3 seconds of sliding on blocks.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.rooted_boots.description: Grants the relic bearer the mysterious power of a sheep.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.rooted_boots.ability.devo: Every %1$s seconds transforms the grass block beneath the player into dirt, restoring 1 hunger and saturation point.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.rooted_boots.leveling_sou: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.warp_drive.description: Allows the relic bearer to teleport their body over short distances.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.warp_drive.ability.telepo: Teleports the player to a position along their line of sight within %1$s blocks, then goes on a cooldown for %2$s seconds.
Line of sight to teleport position
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.warp_drive.leveling_sourc: +%1$s experience points for every 10 blocks traversed using the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.charm_of_shrinking.descri: Allows the relic bearer to shrink their body to access previously unreachable areas.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.whoopee_cushion.descripti: Mysteriously increases the relic bearer's flatulence, leading to entirely unpredictable outcomes.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.whoopee_cushion.ability.p: Has a %1$s%% chance to knock back entities within a %2$s block radius, applying a 10-second nausea effect when taking damage or crouching frequently.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.whoopee_cushion.leveling_: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.kitty_slippers.descriptio: Grants the relic bearer feline traits, including soft paws and countless lives.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.kitty_slippers.ability.pa: Scares away all Creepers and Phantoms near the player.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.kitty_slippers.ability.fa: Increases safe falling height by %1$s blocks.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.kitty_slippers.leveling_s: +%1$s experience points for each fall made safe by the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.kitty_slippers.ability.re: Has a %1$s%% chance to save the player from fatal damage, leaving them with 1 health point.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.kitty_slippers.leveling_s: +%1$s experience points for each point of damage from the last fatal attack prevented by the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.bunny_hoppers.description: Strengthens the relic bearer's legs, allowing them to push off the ground more powerfully.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.bunny_hoppers.ability.hol: Allows high jumps by continuously holding the jump key for up to %1$s seconds.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.bunny_hoppers.leveling_so: +%1$s experience points for each high jump performed using the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.charm_of_sinking.descript: Grants the relic bearer's legs the ability to absorb air from the ground.
While the player stands on the underwater floor, it blocks air consumption and slowly restores its supply by %1$s seconds every second.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.charm_of_sinking.leveling: +%1$s experience points for each touch of the underwater floor.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.panic_necklace.descriptio: Quickens the relic bearer's heartbeat, warning of impending danger.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.panic_necklace.ability.pa: Increases the player's movement speed by %1$s%% for each mob within a %2$s blocks radius targeting the player for attack.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.panic_necklace.leveling_s: +%1$s experience points for each instance of damage taken from mobs affected by the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.helium_flamingo.descripti: Temporarily allows the relic bearer to glide through air as they would water.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.helium_flamingo.ability.f: When performing a double jump, allows the player to float in the air for up to %1$s seconds. Movement speed in the air is proportional to the player's swimming speed with an additional bonus of %2$s%%.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.helium_flamingo.leveling_: +%1$s experience points for each second of air swimming using the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.pocket_piston.description: Grants the relic bearer's hands the strength of mechanisms.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.pocket_piston.ability.dis: Increases knockback in melee attacks by %1$s%%.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.pocket_piston.ability.int: Increases maximum interaction range with the world by %1$s%%.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.pocket_piston.leveling_so: +%1$s experience points for each melee attack performed.
+%1$s experience points for each interaction with the world at the %2$s ability's extended range.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.obsidian_skull.descriptio: Redirects heat aimed at harming the relic bearer onto itself.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.obsidian_skull.ability.he: Completely absorbs damage from fire sources for up to %1$s seconds. If the player has not taken fire damage for 3 seconds, the absorption time regenerates each second.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.obsidian_skull.leveling_s: +%1$s experience points for each second of fire damage absorption using the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.fire_gauntlet.description: Grants the relic bearer’s weapon the powers of the fire element.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.fire_gauntlet.ability.cas: When attacking, releases several sparks that home in on nearby targets, igniting them for %3$s seconds and dealing %2$s%% of the performed attack's damage. The number of sparks is determined through repeated checks of a %1$s%% chance. Each successful check releases one additional spark, but the process stops as soon as the chance fails even once.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.fire_gauntlet.leveling_so: +%1$s experience points for each target hit by a spark from the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.pickaxe_heater.descriptio: Concentrates surrounding heat precisely onto the relic bearer's tools.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.pickaxe_heater.ability.he: Smelts any mined block if possible, consuming one charge from a buffer with a capacity of %1$s units. The buffer regenerates 1 charge every %2$s seconds.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.pickaxe_heater.leveling_s: +%1$s experience points for each block smelted by the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.chorus_totem.description: Allows the relic bearer to rewind time when making rash decisions.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.chorus_totem.ability.past: Each attack against the relic bearer has a %1$s%% chance per percent of missing health to teleport the attacker to a random location within a %2$s block radius.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.chorus_totem.leveling_sou: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.running_shoes.description: Strengthens the relic bearer's legs, allowing them to move faster.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.running_shoes.ability.run: Increases the player's running speed by %1$s%%.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.running_shoes.leveling_so: +%1$s experience points for each second of running.
rarcompat.tooltip.relics.flippers.description: Strengthens the relic bearer's legs, allowing them to swim faster.
Increases the player's swimming speed by %1$s%%.
+%1$s experience points for each second of swimming.

reliquified_ars_nouveau.reliquified_ars_nouveau.can_not_set_spel: The applied spell must start with the 'Touch' form!
reliquified_ars_nouveau.reliquified_ars_nouveau.has_low_level_re: The number of components in the applied spell exceeds the limit allowed by the emblem!
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.cloak_of_concealment.desc: A cloak woven from special mana-infused fabric, capable of concentrating nearby mana into a durable barrier impervious to any weapon.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.cloak_of_concealment.abil: Absorbs all incoming damage by consuming %1$s mana per 1 point of damage. When the player's mana drops to a critical level where absorption becomes impossible, the ability goes on cooldown for %2$s seconds.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.cloak_of_concealment.leve: +%1$s experience points for each instance of absorbing 1.5 or more damage using the %2$s ability.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.flaming_bracer.descriptio: A part of the legendary flaming armor, capable of conjuring magical flames from a victim's body even without the rest of its set.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.flaming_bracer.ability.py: When dealing melee damage to a burning target, there is a %1$s%% chance to release magical fire from it. If triggered successfully, the ability repeats, releasing an additional burst of magical fire and continuing until the chance fails. Maximum triggers: %2$s.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.flaming_bracer.ability.re: Grants the player complete immunity to magical fire damage.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.flaming_bracer.leveling_s: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.ring_of_the_spectral_walk: An unusual ring inlaid with special spectral diamonds, renowned for their ability to phase through any material.

When activated, turns nearby blocks into spectral ones, consuming %1$s mana per second. While inside spectral blocks, the player can move forward in the direction they are looking, ignoring gravity and fall damage. If the ability ends while the player is in an unsafe location, they will be teleported to the last safe spot encountered.
+%1$s experience points for each second of using the %2$s ability.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.quantum_bubble.descriptio: A weightless device that envelops any object it touches.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.quantum_bubble.ability.st: When an enemy projectile appears within a 2-block radius, an aura activates for up to %1$s seconds, halting and trapping all hostile projectiles in bubbles for %2$s seconds. Once the aura expires, the ability goes on cooldown for %3$s seconds.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.quantum_bubble.leveling_s: +%1$s experience points for each projectile trapped in a bubble by the %2$s ability.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.emblem_of_assault.descrip: An elegant brooch in the shape of a sword. By channeling the flow through itself, it concentrates it into its wielder’s weapon.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.emblem_of_assault.ability: Automatically applies the linked spell to the attacked target, then goes on cooldown for %1$s seconds. To use this ability, a spell must be inscribed onto the item using the Scribe’s Table, consisting of no more than %2$s components and starting with the 'Touch' form.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.emblem_of_assault.levelin: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.emblem_of_defense.descrip: An elegant brooch in the shape of a shield. By channeling the flow through itself, it envelops its wearer in a thin yet strong protective film.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.emblem_of_defense.ability: Automatically applies the linked spell to an enemy attacking the player, then goes on cooldown for %1$s seconds. To use this ability, a spell must be inscribed onto the item using the Scribe’s Table, consisting of no more than %2$s components and starting with the 'Touch' form.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.emblem_of_defense.levelin: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.mana_ring.description: A golden ring inlaid with a massive flowstone capable of absorbing and channeling immense amounts of mana.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.mana_ring.ability.empower: Increases the player's maximum mana by %1$s points and its regeneration by %2$s points per second.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.mana_ring.leveling_source: +%1$s experience points for every 20 mana spent on a spell.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.ring_of_thrift.descriptio: At first glance, an ordinary golden ring with a few small pink gemstones. However, their arrangement is not random—they somehow manage to retain the wearer's outgoing mana, preserving and returning it.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.ring_of_thrift.ability.th: When casting a spell, there is a %1$s%% chance that no mana will be consumed.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.ring_of_thrift.leveling_s: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.archmage_glove.descriptio: The secret of great wizards who could cast hundreds of spells without feeling the slightest fatigue. Though, once the secret is revealed... Can they still be called wizards? More like illusionists...
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.archmage_glove.ability.mu: When casting a spell, there is a %1$s%% chance to cast it again. If the effect triggers, the spell is used again, continuing until the chance fails. Each repetition does not consume mana, but the total number of repetitions cannot exceed 5. Works on spells with trail colors in the pink spectrum.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.archmage_glove.leveling_s: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.horn_of_the_wild_hunter.d: One of the horns from the head of a massive wolf, whose howl could summon hounds to its aid.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.horn_of_the_wild_hunter.a: Summons 2 invulnerable wolves that fight alongside the player. Each wolf deals an additional %1$s damage.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.horn_of_the_wild_hunter.l: +%1$s experience for each attack made by a wolf from the %2$s ability.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.spiked_cloak.description: A heavy cloak woven from chimera hide, with sharp orange spikes protruding in places.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.spiked_cloak.ability.spik: When taking damage equal to %1$s%% of the player’s maximum health, fires several spikes, each dealing %2$s damage. If the ability has triggered within the last %3$s seconds, spike damage is doubled for each activation, and the cooldown timer resets. If the timer expires, the bonus damage multiplier resets.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.spiked_cloak.leveling_sou: +%1$s experience for each activation of the %2$s ability.
A wing belonging to either a giant bat or some other monstrous creature...
Performing a double jump puts the player into Elytra flight mode. Pressing the jump key again triggers a forward dash of %1$s blocks. Up to %2$s consecutive dashes can be performed before landing.
+%1$s experience for each second of flight using the %2$s ability.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.whirlisprig_petals.descri: A sprout eerily similar to the ones growing on the heads of whirlisprigs... How terrifying...
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.whirlisprig_petals.abilit: Holding the jump key gently lifts the player upwards for up to %1$s seconds. When falling from a dangerous height, automatically grants the Slow Falling effect.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.whirlisprig_petals.leveli: +%1$s experience for each full ascent to maximum height using the %2$s ability.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.whirling_broom.descriptio: The name of this broom and the suspicious resemblance of its bristles to whirlisprig petals bring about some eerily unsettling thoughts... However, aside from that, it’s a fantastic means of transportation!
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.whirling_broom.ability.br: Summons a broom controlled by standard movement keys. Its flight height cannot exceed %1$s blocks above ground. The broom has %4$s health, regenerating every 5 seconds. If its health is fully depleted, it disappears and the ability goes on a 1-minute cooldown. Holding the sprint key consumes %2$s mana per second and increases speed by %3$s%%.
Proper conditions to summon the broom
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.whirling_broom.leveling_s: +%1$s experience per second of flight while riding a broom summoned by %2$s.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.ring_of_last_will.descrip: A ring with a majestic gem that hides the fragility of reality itself – shatter it, and the boundaries of time and space collapse, unleashing temporal paradoxes.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.ring_of_last_will.ability: Upon taking fatal damage, protects the player from death by rewinding time by 3 seconds, then goes on cooldown for %1$s seconds.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.ring_of_last_will.levelin: +%1$s XP for each activation of the %2$s ability.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.ballistarian_bracer.descr: The bracer of a legendary warlord from ages past, whose regiment was composed solely of archers. Despite lacking any form of melee defense, he never knew a single defeat throughout his history.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.ballistarian_bracer.abili: Summons up to %2$s floating bows behind the player. When the player fires a ranged weapon, each floating bow has a %3$s%% chance to also fire, dealing %1$s damage to the target. Each floating bow has 1 health and, if destroyed, will only be resummoned after %4$s seconds.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.ballistarian_bracer.level: +%1$s experience for each hit on a target by a bow from the %2$s ability.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.illusionists_mantle.descr: A garment that masterfully deceives mortal eyes, making them see many silhouettes where only one figure is hidden.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.illusionists_mantle.abili: When taking damage from a living entity, has a %1$s%% chance to create a player illusion on the opposite side of the attacker, lasting up to %2$s seconds. If the player takes fatal damage, they are protected from death and swapped with the farthest illusion.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.illusionists_mantle.level: +%1$s XP for each illusion created by the %2$s ability.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.architects_staff.descript: A majestic cane crafted from mysterious material, its refined headpiece capable of erecting phantom bridges that fill voids in the world’s landscape.
Has a durability of %2$s, regenerating 1 point every %1$s seconds. Hold right-click while looking at a block to set it as the first point, then release right-click while looking at another block to set the second point, creating a temporary bridge between them (max length %3$s blocks) for 1 minute, consuming 1 durability.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.architects_staff.leveling: +%1$s XP for each bridge created by the %2$s ability.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.emblem_of_devotion.descri: An elegant brooch in the shape of a heart. Channeling energy through itself, it concentrates it into a sphere that orbits its bearer, forming a boundary against foes.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.emblem_of_devotion.abilit: Summons one orbital sphere with a linked spell every %1$s seconds, which casts the spell on a target upon collision. The total number of spheres cannot exceed %2$s. To function, the item must be inscribed using a Scribe's Table with a spell consisting of no more than %3$s components, and must begin with the 'Touch' form.
reliquified_ars_nouveau.tooltip.relics.emblem_of_devotion.leveli: +%1$s XP for each collision of an orbital sphere from the %2$s ability with a target.

reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.scouring_eye.description: An eye torn from the socket of one of the legendary End monsters. Despite the years passed, it is still alive and searching for a target for its next battle...
reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.scouring_eye.ability.glow: Remembers the last target attacked by the player for %2$s seconds. When the ability is activated, the player is teleported behind the remembered target and the ability goes on cooldown for %1$s seconds.
reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.scouring_eye.leveling_sou: +%1$s XP for each teleportation to a target using the %2$s ability.
reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.void_vortex_in_bottle.des: A homework assignment of a student from the infamous magic school where students face deadly trials, capturing lightning, clouds, or vortexes in jars...
reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.void_vortex_in_bottle.abi: Upon killing a target, summons a void vortex %1$s blocks tall that pulls in nearby targets and goes on cooldown for %3$s seconds. After 5 seconds, the vortex explodes, dealing %2$s damage to all nearby targets. If a weaker or equal vortex is nearby, it absorbs it, growing in size and extending its duration.
reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.void_vortex_in_bottle.lev: +%1$s XP for each void vortex created by the %2$s ability.
reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.void_cloak.description: A robe belonging to a mage who, according to legend, lived beneath the bedrock of any known world. There he mastered a never-before-seen magic of void runes and defeated a massive End beast, whose eye still roams in search of battle.
reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.void_cloak.ability.void_i: Grants complete immunity to void damage.
reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.void_cloak.ability.void_r: Every %1$s seconds, summons a void rune under a random nearby target, dealing %2$s damage.
reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.void_cloak.ability.seismi: Upon the death of the player or their controlled creature, summons a seismic zone at the death location with a radius of %1$s blocks, triggering void runes up to %2$s times, each dealing %3$s damage.
reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.void_cloak.leveling_sourc: +%1$s XP for each activation of the %2$s ability.
+%1$s XP for each activation of the %2$s ability.
reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.vacuum_glove.description: One of the filthiest tools, not wielded by warriors or mages, but by 'butchers'. Its aura liquefies the air around it, hindering both movement and mind.
reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.vacuum_glove.ability.vacu: Creates an area around the player with a radius of %2$s blocks that slows all targets trying to escape it by %1$s%% at the edge. The slowdown increases the closer a target is to the boundary.
reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.vacuum_glove.leveling_sou: +%1$s XP for every 10 seconds of slowdown from the %2$s ability.
reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.void_bubble.description: A fragile yet durable device that protects the head, body, and mind all at once.
reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.void_bubble.ability.prote: Encases the player's head in a protective bubble, completely eliminating the need for air. The bubble also blocks up to %1$s incoming attacks before exploding, scattering %2$s shards in all directions, each dealing %3$s damage. It then regenerates after %4$s seconds.
reliquified_lenders_cataclysm.tooltip.relics.void_bubble.leveling_sour: +%1$s XP for each attack blocked by the %2$s ability.

reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.minotaur_hoof.description: The hoof of a beast that guarded the heart of the underground labyrinth. Rumored to grant its wearer the speed and endurance of the frenzied minotaurs.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.minotaur_hoof.ability.mom: While sprinting, gradually increases the player's movement speed up to %1$s%%. After 3 seconds of running, once the player reaches maximum speed, incoming damage is reduced by %2$s%%, and all nearby targets are knocked back and take %3$s damage until the player stops running.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.minotaur_hoof.leveling_so: +%1$s experience points for each instance of damage dealt using the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.hydra_heart.description: The most valuable part of the multi-headed fire-breathing serpent that dwells somewhere in the fiery depths of the Twilight Forest. Though its original owner is long dead, the heart still beats, dripping with searing blood.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.hydra_heart.ability.hydra: When taking damage, has a %1$s%% chance to drop a blood droplet that, upon landing, creates a damaging area for %3$s seconds, dealing %2$s damage to all targets and igniting them for 5 seconds.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.hydra_heart.leveling_sour: +%1$s experience points for each blood droplet created by the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.item.reliquified_twilight_forest.gem.tip: Can be used to inlay the Lich Crown
Can be used to inlay the Lich Crown or to craft wands
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.description: The crown of the Twilight Forest’s very own king - the Lich. A symbol of his power and dominance. Legend has it that the true potential of this relic can only be unlocked by uniting all ten gems...
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.ability.soulbo: Allows the crown to be inlaid with %1$s special gems. Each unique gem unlocks a new ability, while additional gems of the same type increase the level of the corresponding ability. To insert a gem into the crown, right-click it while holding it in your inventory. To remove a gem, ensure your cursor is empty and right-click the crown.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.ability.bone_p: All skeletons become friendly towards the player.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.ability.fortif: Every %2$s seconds, creates a shield around the player that completely blocks most directed attacks. The number of active shields cannot exceed %1$s at a time.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.ability.lifedr: When the player's health falls below 20%, for 5 seconds, drains %1$s%% of their max health from all targets within %2$s blocks. Afterward, it enters a cooldown of %3$s seconds.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.ability.twilig: When looking at a target and pressing LMB, launches a twilight projectile moving at approximately %2$s blocks per second, dealing %1$s damage. Does not work if the target is within melee range.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.ability.zombie: Every %3$s seconds, spawns a mini-zombie that fights for the player, dealing %2$s damage to targets. The total number of mini-zombies cannot exceed %1$s.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.leveling_sourc: Fortification
+%1$s experience points for each shield created by the %2$s ability.
Will to Live
+%1$s experience points for every 0.5 seconds of healing done by the %2$s ability.
Twilight Touch
+%1$s experience points for each hit landed with the projectile from the %2$s ability.
Risen Servants
+%1$s experience points for each mini-zombie spawned by the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.firefly_queen.description: A fragile and slightly disgusting-looking insect capable of spawning a swarm of fireflies that will forever dispel any darkness.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.firefly_queen.ability.glo: Generates a firefly larva in the internal buffer every %1$s seconds, with a maximum of %2$s at a time. When the player is in complete darkness, it consumes 1 larva and places a firefly nearby to light the way.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.firefly_queen.leveling_so: +%1$s experience points for each firefly placed by the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.cicada_bottle.description: A jar filled with the energy of hatred. Though this spawn of evil looks like a small bug, do not let your eyes deceive you. Its devilish song can evoke true rage in anyone who hears it, making them willing to do anything to make it stop.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.cicada_bottle.ability.cic: Has a %1$s%% chance on hit to inflict the Cicada's Curse on the target for %2$s seconds, forcing all nearby mobs to attack that target, ignoring their other tasks.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.cicada_bottle.leveling_so: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.deer_antler.description: A suspiciously large antler for an ordinary deer, which would look just as suspiciously fitting on some living creature.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.deer_antler.ability.ride_: When used on a creature whose hitbox volume does not exceed %1$s blocks, places it on the player's antlers and prevents it from dealing damage to the player.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.deer_antler.leveling_sour: +%1$s experience points for every 3 seconds spent with a creature on the antlers from the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.scaled_cloak.description: A cloak woven from giant serpent scales not only takes on the shape of its previous owner but also inherits some of her abilities.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.scaled_cloak.ability.wall: Allows the player to smoothly climb walls for %1$s seconds. After the duration ends, the player will slowly slide down.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.scaled_cloak.ability.elus: When taking damage, has a %1$s%% chance to make the attacker miss if the player maintains eye contact with them.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.scaled_cloak.leveling_sou: +%1$s experience points for each second of climbing from the %2$s ability.
+%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.twilight_feather.descript: A feather from the tail of a mysterious bird that could transform into other creatures.
When attacking a target whose current health does not exceed the player's maximum health, there is a %1$s%% chance to instantly execute it, transforming it into a small bird.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.twilight_feather.leveling: +%1$s experience points for each successful activation of the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.thorn_crown.description: An ornament closely tied to torment. Its sharp thorns dig into the wearer's head, bringing both unbearable pain and paralyzing power.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.thorn_crown.ability.pokin: Upon touching a target, deals %3$s damage and has a %1$s%% chance to paralyze them for %2$s seconds.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.thorn_crown.ability.thorn: Grants the player full resistance to any 'thorn' damage.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.thorn_crown.leveling_sour: +%1$s experience points for each paralysis triggered by the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.steel_cape.description: A remarkably flexible yet durable material forms the basis of this cape, providing not only protection for its wearer but also retaliation when their safety is threatened.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.steel_cape.ability.iron_g: When taking damage that could potentially be mitigated by armor (even if none is equipped), reduces it by %1$s points. If the damage is not fully blocked, there is a %2$s%% chance to launch a steel orb toward the attacker, dealing %3$s damage to all in its path and stunning them for %4$s seconds.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.steel_cape.leveling_sourc: +%1$s experience points for each steel orb released by the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.charm_backpack.descriptio: A seemingly ordinary backpack, yet for some unknown reason, charms inside it behave differently...
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.charm_backpack.ability.ch: Allows storing up to %1$s life or inventory charms inside the backpack. When a charm activates, it prevents complete destruction and instead goes on cooldown for %2$s minutes per its level. To store a charm, right-click on the backpack in the inventory with it. To extract a charm, the cursor must be empty.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.charm_backpack.leveling_s: +%1$s experience points for each activation of the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.goblin_nose.description: A nose crudely taken from a goblin. No one suspected that goblins could shed skin like lizards...
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.goblin_nose.ability.vein_: When activated, worsens vision but enhances smell, allowing the detection of valuable ores within a %1$s block radius. Also allows storing up to %2$s ore blocks inside the nose, so the sense only recognizes them. To store ore, right-click the nose in the inventory with it. To extract ore, the cursor must be empty.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.goblin_nose.leveling_sour: +%1$s experience points for each ore mined under the effect of the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.giant_glove.description: A piece of gear once worn by fairy-tale giants who dwell in cloud-top huts. It's said the only way to reach them is with magic beans whose stalk pierces the skies...
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.giant_glove.ability.overs: Increases the size and stats of the held item by %1$s%%.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.giant_glove.leveling_sour: +%1$s XP for each block broken or entity hit made with an item enhanced by %2$s.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.chromatic_cloak.descripti: A stylish and vibrant cloak, woven from the wool of a mythical rainbow sheep...
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.chromatic_cloak.ability.w: Stores up to %1$s slots of wool with up to %2$s units each. Every wool color grants a specific effect, applied for %3$s seconds if not already active, consuming one unit of wool. To insert wool, right-click the cloak in inventory with wool; to extract, make sure the cursor holds no item.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.chromatic_cloak.ability.e: Increases the effect level based on the number of identical-colored wool slots, up to a maximum level of %1$s.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.chromatic_cloak.leveling_: +%1$s XP for each level of effect granted by the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.ability.frostb: Applies a stacking frostbite effect for %1$s seconds on attack. Once the effect exceeds 7 seconds, the target takes 1 damage through armor every 2 seconds until the effect ends.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.leveling_sourc: Frostbite
+%1$s XP for each frostbite effect applied by %2$s.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.maple_syrup_bottle.descri: An endless syrup bottle that occasionally conjures up fresh waffles.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.maple_syrup_bottle.abilit: Eating a waffle increases health regeneration by %2$s%% for %3$s seconds; the effect stacks. There's a %1$s%% chance the waffle won't be consumed.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.invisibility_cloak.descri: A strange thing – stare at it long enough and it... starts vanishing? Hard to imagine why the emperor needed such a cloak...
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.invisibility_cloak.abilit: Hides the appearance of equipped armor.
Grants full invisibility after remaining completely still or sneaking without interruption for at least %1$s seconds.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.invisibility_cloak.leveli: +%1$s XP for each activation of the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.parasite_115.description: ...deep within the prison chambers of the §kDark§r Tower, inmate number 115 was forcibly infected with an unknown §kparasite§r. The §klarva§r entwined with his body, feeding on his §kmind§r and flesh until only a twisted mass of reddish §krot§r remained. The warped minds of the wardens immediately forced the §kunfortunate soul§r from the neighboring cell to taste the result. He resisted, but once a piece touched his tongue...
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.parasite_115.ability.infe: Has a %1$s%% chance to infect the attacked target with a parasite, which, if the target is not attacked again within 5 seconds, delivers %2$s rapid strikes dealing %3$s damage each. If the target is killed by the parasite's attack, a random amount of §kExperiment 115§r will drop, up to %4$s units.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.parasite_115.leveling_sou: +%1$s XP for each parasite infection caused by the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.parasite_116.description: ...suddenly he began to tremble, his body arching as if §ksomething§r inside tried to break free. His eyes turned white, and with a mad roar he attacked a warden, then another, and another... until no one remained in his path. He awoke deep within the §kwilderness§r of the Twilight Forest - wounded, barefoot, covered in blood. Who knows if it was his last meal to blame, or if he is now the victim of a new experiment - §k116§r.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.parasite_116.ability.infe: Has a %1$s%% chance to infect the attacked target with a parasite, which, if the target is not attacked again within 5 seconds, delivers %2$s rapid strikes dealing %3$s damage each. If the target is killed by the parasite's attack, a random amount of §kExperiment 115§r will drop, up to %4$s units.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.parasite_116.ability.rage: Consuming §kExperiment 115§r restores %1$s%% rage charge, which is consumed at a rate of 10%% per second. Rage increases the player's movement speed, attack speed, and damage. At 100%% rage, the bonus reaches %2$s%%.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.parasite_116.leveling_sou: +%1$s XP for each parasite infection caused by the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.ability.mirror: Any attack on the player has a %1$s%% chance to be reflected back to the attacker, healing the player for the amount of damage dealt.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.leveling_sourc: Mirror Leech
+%1$s XP for each full unit of damage reflected using the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.ability.vendet: Attacking a target that damaged the player in the last %1$s seconds increases damage by %2$s%%.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.leveling_sourc: Vendetta
+%1$s XP for each attack with increased damage from the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.ability.biome_: Increases damage dealt by %1$s%% for every 0.1 unit of biome temperature where the player is located.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.leveling_sourc: Heat Concentration
+%1$s XP for each attack with bonus damage from the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.ability.ethere: Any projectile aimed at the player passes through without causing harm. After %1$s deflections, the ability goes on cooldown for %2$s seconds.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.leveling_sourc: Ethereal Transformation
+%1$s XP for each projectile deflected using the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.ability.frenzy: Attacking different targets consecutively increases damage by %1$s%% per hit. Damaging a previously attacked target or not attacking for more than 5 seconds resets the bonus. Killing a target while the effect is active resets the target list without losing the accumulated bonus.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.leveling_sourc: Frenzy
+%1$s XP for each bonus gained from the %2$s ability.
reliquified_twilight_forest.tooltip.relics.lich_crown.ability.twilig: Grants full immortality within the boundaries of the Twilight Forest.

starbunclemania.starbunclemania.page.star_battery: Allows Starbuncles to transport energy. Once wearing the accessory, use the Dominion wand to connect them between FE blocks.
starbunclemania.starbunclemania.page.star_bin: Allows Starbuncles to embrace their inner raccoon and trash items. While wearing the accessory the Starbuncle will void any nearby item on the ground.

starbunclemania.starbunclemania.page.star_hat: Accessories from StarbuncleMania aren't just for the worker starbuncles to enjoy, you can use them on your starbuncle familiar too! starbunclemania.starbunclemania.page.star_saddle: Allows Starbuncles to transport players. While wearing the accessory, the Starbuncle becomes big enough to be rideable. [Still a bit wip, might be a bit wonky]
starbunclemania.starbunclemania.page.wixie_cook: The Wixie can now cook! Place a Wixie on a furnace to allow it to smelt and smoke items, also compatible with a cooking pot [Farmers Delight] and crucibles [EidolonRepraised] to automate them.
starbunclemania.starbunclemania.page.wixie_cut: Place a Wixie charm on a stonecutter or on a cutting board to have it use their cutting recipes for craftings.
starbunclemania.starbunclemania.page.wixie_mixer: Place a Wixie charm on a fluid jar to convert it to a different type of cauldron. starbunclemania.starbunclemania.page.wyrm_degree: Allows Starbuncles to insert/extract items from a specific side with Direction Scrolls.
starbunclemania.starbunclemania.robin_mask.tooltip: Tweaks the starbuncle's item transport to round-robin items between inventories, also stops pickup. Can be used as a simple cosmetic by sneaking while using it, without changing its current behavior.
starbunclemania.starbunclemania.simple_cosmetic.tooltip: Simple cosmetic for your familiars. Supported familiars: Starbuncle, Wixie, Drygmy, Bookwyrm.
starbunclemania.starbunclemania.trash_bin.tooltip: Changes a starbuncle's job to void the items it pickups and from linked chests. Can be used as a simple cosmetic by sneaking while using it, without changing its current behavior.

tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.card_cra: Location Cards are created from Iron Ingots and any Dye. The recipe produces 4 Location Cards. Alternatively one may substitute the iron for an ingot of %s and receive 16 cards from the same recipe.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.card_ove: Location Cards record spatial coordinates for use in multiversal devices.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.card_usa: To write location data to a card, a %s or %s is required at the correct coordinates or a standard issue %s with the coordinates already saved inside. Right-clicking the card onto a %s or %s will link the card to the device. Right-clicking the card onto the information panel for a location saved inside the %s will write the location data to the card.

Written cards can be used to supply location data to a %s or a %s. Cards obtained from other players only function with the %s if placed into a carried %s, however all cards can be freely used with the %s.
Placing a written Location Card into the crafting grid will wipe the data stored on the card allowing it to be reused.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.cell_cra: Chronon Cells can be created with materials on hand, such as Iron Ingots, Copper Ingots, Redstone Dust, and Amethyst Shards.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.cell_ove: Chronons are essential fuel for TVA multiversal technology, thus the first step to recreating this technology is generating and storing Chronons. Primitive Chronon Cells can store Chronons and be used as materials for more advanced technology.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.cell_usa: Empty Chronon Cells can be charged slowly over time if carried alongside a %s or a %s, or they can be placed inside a %s. Charged Chronon Cells will transfer their stored Chronons to all carried devices automatically, so long as they are all present in the main inventory or curio slots. Chronon Cells hold {X} Chronons.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.chronoma: Chronomarks are crafted from a Block of Iron, Iron Ingots, ingots of %s, an Ender Pearl, and a block of Tinted Glass.

The Chronomark is a stationary block used to generate exact spatial coordinates and provide them to other devices. As an upgrade over %s, Chronomarks allow for an offset of up to %s blocks to be specified in case the user wants to mount the device on a high ceiling or bury the device under the floor. They also allow for more user filtering options.

To write data to a %s, place the Chronomark and right-click it with a %s. The card will then be written and can be used with %s. The %s displays Chronomarks and %ss owned by the user automatically, but written %ss can be shared with others.

Filters can be set on the Chronomark to only allow certain users to freely access the device based on available and compatible team or guild frameworks. Right-clicking the device with an empty hand brings up an interface where device name, Timedoor color, security options, and offsets can be configured.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.chronome: Chronometers can be created from any basic Clock, along with a few extra components. Also required will be a block of Tinted Glass, ingots of %s, and a %s.

Chronometers are a Chronon generation device carried by the user to passively generate Chronons for their other devices. Properly crafted Chronometers generate Chronons at a faster rate than primitive solutions.

Kept in the main inventory or a curio slot, a Chronometer or %s will invert the temporal decay of local background radiation to synthesize Chronons, which are then distributed to all carried devices or storage cells automatically, so long as they are all present in the main inventory or curio slots.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.chronon_: Chronon Batteries can be created with %s, Iron Ingots, %ss, and Amethyst Shards, to power multiversal devices, and are the ideal way to carry Chronons on the go.
Chronon Batteries are devices for storing Chronons made from smaller cells. They hold more Chronons than individual %ss.

Empty Chronon Batteries can be charged slowly over time if carried alongside a %s or a %s, or they can be placed inside a %s. Charged Chronon Batteries will transfer their stored Chronons to all carried devices automatically, so long as they are all present in the main inventory or curio slots. Chronon Batteries hold %s Chronons.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.chronong: Chronon Generators can be created from any basic Clock, along with a block of Glass, Iron Ingots, and a %s
A Chronon Generator is a primitive device capable of generating Chronons for use with other devices.

Kept in the main inventory or a curio slot, a Chronon Generator or %s will invert the temporal decay of local background radiation to synthesize Chronons, which are then distributed to all carried devices or storage cells automatically, so long as they are all present in the main inventory or curio slots.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.location: Location Broadcasters are crafted with a block of Glass, an Emerald, a measure of Redstone Dust, a Compass, and an Iron Ingot.
The Location Broadcaster allow lost agents to be found and rescued by agents with specially upgraded %s.

The device can be used in the hand to toggle between its modes of operation. The screen on the device will glow green if teleportation is enabled, and will glow red if disabled. This allows the carrier to decide when they are open to Timedoors being opened to their location.
If a Location Broadcaster is carried in the inventory or curio slot and is turned on, the carrier will appearin the list of possible teleports for %s with the Teleport to Players upgrade.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.marker_c: They are crafted from a Block of Iron, Iron Ingots, an Ender Pearl, and a block of Glass.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.marker_o: The Timedoor Marker is used to generate exact spatial coordinates and provide them to other devices.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.marker_u: To write data to a %s, place the Timedoor Marker and right-click it with a %s. The card will then be written and can be used with the %s. The %s displays Timedoor Markers and %ss owned by the user automatically, but %ss linked to devices can be shared with others.
Right-clicking the device with an empty hand brings up an interface where device name, Timedoor color, and security options can be configured.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.metronom: Once booted, the Metronome will begin to generate Chronons into its own internal battery, which holds %s Chronons. Right-clicking the device will bring up the interface, where devices can be placed to store Chronons via the left-hand slots or take Chronons via the right-hand slots. Additionally, the Metronome is coded to the user’s temporal aura, and may be locked to prevent unauthorized access via the lock button in the upper right. It is locked by default.
Metronomes are crafted with Ingots of %s, Chronon Batteries, and an Ender Chest.

If the user places additional Metronomes, after booting they will link with existing Metronomes owned by the user in a multiversal network, combining their maximum storage capacities. Linked Metronomes will also combine charging power to generate more Chronons with each pulse.
Metronomes are a Chronon generation device that can be placed in the world to provide a stationary solution to charging devices and storing Chronons.

Generally, Metronomes cannot be charged within the inventory, and instead need to be placed into the world. There is an initial charge of Chronons needed to boot the device and gain access to its functionality after it is placed. This boot charge can be provided from a %s or %s in hand by crouch-right-clicking the Metronome.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.projecto: Timedoor Projectors are crafted from Copper Ingots, a Glass block, an Ender Pearl, a %s and Blocks of Iron.

When a standard issue %s is unavailable, rudimentary versions of the device can be crafted using materials on hand. The Timedoor Projector is the most basic device capable of allowing teleportation via Timedoors.
Timedoors are doorways between two points in space and/or time. They appear as glowing panels of glass, and can be passed through in either direction like any other doorway.
Timedoors consume Chronons from the Timedoor Projector upon generation and appear for a set amount of time before closing automatically.

Timedoor Projectors allow for the creation of Timedoors to spatial coordinates read from %ss. These can be loaded into the device by right-clicking the card onto the Timedoor Projector while it is either in the inventory or placed in the world, or by right-clicking a card in the inventory while holding the projector with the cursor. Cards can be retrieved from the device by either right-clicking it on an empty inventory space, or by right-clicking the device where it is placed in the world.

The device can be activated while held by using it (right-click). Holding crouch and using the device will place it on the block being looked at. Placing the Timedoor Projector allows it to be triggered by a Redstone signal instead, such as from an adjacent button.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.screenin: Screening Devices are crafted with a block of Tinted Glass, an Emerald, a measure of Redstone Dust, a Compass, and an ingot of %s.
The Screening Device is an advanced version of the %s that features more advanced filtering capability.

On a surface level, the Screening Device provides the same functionality as the %s, allowing users with upgraded %s to open Timedoors directly to their location. Additionally, the Screening Device can also filter who is given this permission based on available and compatible team or guild frameworks. Holding the device and right-click using it will cycle the device through its available modes.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.tempad_a: The New Location app allows the user to save their current coordinates in the Tempad to allow for travel via the Teleport app. A map is present on the screen to help users find their bearings when saving locations. The location can be named before saving, and the user may also specify a specific color for Timedoors opened to the location.

When docked on a %s, the terminal provides access to the Portal Setup app, allowing for selection of a destination from the user’s docked Tempad, and for precision tweaks to the opened Timedoor’s position and rotation (plus or minus %s blocks from the default position). This app is not available without docking the Tempad. Please see the %s entry for more information.

The Settings app allows users to adjust the behaviour of certain Tempad functions. The function of the Tempad’s macro button can be changed, as well as which app opens by default when the Tempad is opened.

Opening the Teleport app will present the user with a list of locations saved in the device, as well as the %ss or %ss owned by the user. Clicking these entries will populate the info panel to the right of the list, and enable the teleport button. Clicking the Teleport button will consume Chronons and generate a Timedoor to the location specified in the entry.

Next to the search bar, there is a button that will cycle through the available sorting modes. Locations may be sorted by dimension, alphabetical order, or by type. In all modes, locations are sorted into collapsible categories to make the list easier to view.

When a location is selected from the list, and the info panel to the right is populated, two additional buttons display at the bottom of the panel. The pin button will pin the location to the top of the list. Only one location may be pinned at a time. The X button will delete the location from the list. A %s right-clicked onto this information panel will be written with the location data from the saved location.

With a %s docked inside the Tempad, access is gained to the Travel Timeline app. This expands the functionality of the docked %s and gives more granular control, allowing the user to move back along to more points along their timeline instead of being limited to major events.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.tempad_c: The Tempad is crafted with blocks of Tinted Glass, a piece of Nether Quartz, an Ender Pearl, a Redstone Lamp, ingots of %s, and a %s.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.tempad_o: The standard issue Tempad is the single most powerful piece of technology covered in this database. A Tempad can create Timedoors to any coordinates saved in the device, as well as access a docked %s to allow the user to view and move along their personal timeline.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.tempad_t: Timedoors are doorways between two points in space and/or time. They appear as glowing panels of glass, and can be passed through in either direction like any other doorway.

Timedoors consume Chronons from the Tempad upon generation and appear for a set amount of time before closing automatically. %ss given a constant redstone signal will open a door indefinitely for a continuous Chronon cost.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.tempad_u: Holding the Tempad and right-clicking will bring up the Tempad’s interface as well as the user’s inventory. Tempad functionality is organized into apps and presented to the user through the app tray on the left of the interface. Clicking these app buttons will open the appropriate app within the device and give access to all of its powerful functions.
Location data can be added to the Tempad for teleporting via the New Location app. To use %ss with the Tempad, please see the %s.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.time_ste: Time Steel can be acquired in MC-21 and adjacent realms by crafting Netherite Scraps with Iron Ingots. Raw Iron to refine can be found in ore almost anywhere. Acquiring the scraps of Netherite, on the other hand, is contingent on access to a Nether dimension. It is inadvisable to get stuck on a timeline without access to these resources, as developing multiversal technology without it can lead to unstable results.

Time Steel is a crucial component to all advanced multiversal technology, as it is not affected by the passage of time. Thus it is a reliable material to house and shield all of the sensitive components required for traversing space and time.
Depending on the technology available in a given timeline, alternate or more efficient methods to produce Time Steel may be discovered. Recipe repositories may be checked for more details.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.time_twi: It is crafted with ingots of %s, blocks of Tinted Glass, a %s, and an Ender Pearl.
The Time Twister is a hand-held device that allows users to move back along significant events on their personal timeline.

Using the Time Twister in the hand will present the user with a radial display showing points in the user’s past where they changed dimensions or died. Clicking one of the options will teleport the user back to the indicated location. Any points on the timeline forward from the selected point (options counter-clockwise from the selected point) will be destroyed to prevent paradoxes.

Note that if the selected point involves moving the user to a different dimension, new options will appear in the Time Twister for leaving your current dimension and appearing in the new one. This means that in some instances the Time Twister can appear to not be deleting future entries properly, when in fact this is a failure of the user to pay attention.

If more granularity in timeline events is required, the Time Twister can be docked with a %s to provide access to the Travel Timeline app. The Time Twister is docked by right-clicking it onto a %s in the inventory, or by right-clicking a %s onto the Time Twister. This also provides the benefit of carrying the Time Twister without it taking an extra inventory slot.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.travel_a:
For agents dispatched to MC-21 or adjacent realms:

While the technology developed by the TVA is the most advanced in the multiverse, it is not capable of the impossible. Just as time doors cannot be opened to different points of time within the TVA, they cannot be opened to different points of time in MC-21 adjacent realms. Much like the TVA, time passes differently in MC-21 and all related branches, and as such, the TVA's technology is not capable of connecting different points in time within these locations. Spatial travel remains unaffected.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.wallet_c: Card Wallets can be crafted with Copper Ingots, Leather, and a blank %s.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.wallet_o: Card Wallets are a convenient way of storing and carrying a large amount of Location Cards.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.wallet_u: Right click the wallet in hand to open its storage. %ss may be placed in the storage for safe-keeping to keep the inventory from becoming too cluttered.

Once the user obtains a standard %s, Cards inside the wallet are automatically added to the %s’s location list if they are placed inside a carried wallet. Note that this is unnecessary for a %s or a %s owned by the user, as these devices are already added to the user’s %s. What this does enable, however, is the continued sharing of location cards between users, and being able to access these shared cards via the %s’s interface.

Only one Card Wallet can provide locations to the user’s %s at a given time. Priority is placed on the curio slot if available, then hotbar slots from left to right, then inventory slots from left to right, top to bottom.
tempad.item.tempad.knowledge_projector.workstat: It can be crafted with blocks of Tinted Glass, Copper Ingots, ingots of %s, and a piece of Nether Quartz.
The Workstation is a stationary computer terminal that allows the user to accomplish various tasks when a %s is placed on the docking pad.

Docking a %s by right-clicking it onto the docking pad unlocks the cassette slot at the back to allow the use of Upgrade Tapes. Right-clicking an Upgrade Tape into the cassette slot applies the upgrade on the tape to the docked %s, provided the specific upgrade isn’t already present on the device.

When a %s is docked on the docking pad, the terminal to the left is also unlocked, allowing the user to set up a stationary teleportation device. The usage of the Workstation in this way is similar to the %s, in that it accepts a redstone signal from any side and creates a Timedoor for the user.

Right-clicking on the terminal, however, opens a new Portal Setup app, allowing for selection of a destination from the user’s docked %s, and for precision tweaks to the opened Timedoor’s position and rotation (plus or minus %s blocks in any direction from the default position). Additionally, if a constant redstone signal is applied the Timedoors will remain open until the signal stops, after which it will resume its normal countdown to close.
